<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="356" pageId="4" pageNumber="355" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,1889,2024]" lastBlockId="5.[151,1437,151,609]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="356" pageId="4" pageNumber="355">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1889,1915]" pageId="4" pageNumber="355">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Vertex longer at midline than wide, median carina present, evanescent distally. Hind tibiae lacking spines, forecoxae lacking denticle. Lateral pronotal carinae terminating on ventral margin of prothorax, tegulae evident. Medioventral process of the pygofer is subtriangular. Parameres distally bifid in lateral view and acute apex in ventral view with inner lateral tooth near apex. Periandrium (=phalobase) usually ring-like at base of aedeagus, prolonged into a projection of varying form subtending the aedeagus. Anal tube short and stout, distally projecting ventrally of ventrocaudally.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="356" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,609]" pageId="5" pageNumber="356">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,223,249]" pageId="5" pageNumber="356">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Bahder, B. W. &amp; Bartlett, C. R. &amp; Barrantes, E. A. B. &amp; Zumbado, M. A. Z. &amp; Humphries, A. R. &amp; Helmick, E. E. &amp; Goss, E. M. &amp; Ascunce, M. S." box="[323,563,223,249]" pageId="5" pageNumber="356" pagination="1" refId="ref6422" refString="Bahder, B. W., Bartlett, C. R., Barrantes, E. A. B., Zumbado, M. A. Z., Humphries, A. R., Helmick, E. E. Goss, E. M. &amp; Ascunce, M. S. (2019 a) A new genus and species of cixiid planthopper (Hemiptera: Auchenorrhyncha: Fulgoroidea) from the Reserva Privada el Silencio de Los Angeles Cloud Forest in Costa Rica. Zootaxa, 4701 (1), 065 - 081. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4701.1.5" type="journal article" year="2019">
Bahder 
<emphasis box="[411,461,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="356">et al</emphasis>
. (2019a)
</bibRefCitation>
noted that the terminalia of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zumbado Echavarria &amp; Barrantes Barrantes &amp; Bartlett &amp; Helmick &amp; Bahder" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Zumbado Echavarria &amp; Barrantes Barrantes &amp; Bartlett &amp; Helmick &amp; Bahder" baseAuthorityYear="2021" box="[884,975,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Haplaxius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="356" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="delta">
<emphasis box="[884,975,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="356">H. delta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembled those of 
<taxonomicName box="[1203,1365,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Myxia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="356" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="belinda">
<emphasis box="[1203,1365,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="356">Myxia belinda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on the illustrations of 
<bibRefCitation author="Kramer, J. P." box="[399,566,259,285]" pageId="5" pageNumber="356" pagination="301 - 389" refId="ref7308" refString="Kramer, J. P. (1979) Taxonomic study of the planthopper genus Myndus in the Americas (Homoptera: Fulgoroidea: Cixiidae). Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 105 (3), 301 - 389. http: // www. jstor. org / stable / 25078242" type="journal article" year="1979">Kramer (1979)</bibRefCitation>
(specimens were not then available). Serendipitously, a specimen of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zumbado Echavarria &amp; Barrantes Barrantes &amp; Bartlett &amp; Helmick &amp; Bahder" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Zumbado Echavarria &amp; Barrantes Barrantes &amp; Bartlett &amp; Helmick &amp; Bahder" baseAuthorityYear="2021" box="[1346,1436,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Haplaxius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="356" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="delta">
<emphasis box="[1346,1436,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="356">H. delta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was collected in 
<collectingCountry box="[340,467,295,321]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="5" pageNumber="356">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
. The resulting morphological comparison and molecular analysis gives strong support for transferring 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zumbado Echavarria &amp; Barrantes Barrantes &amp; Bartlett &amp; Helmick &amp; Bahder" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Zumbado Echavarria &amp; Barrantes Barrantes &amp; Bartlett &amp; Helmick &amp; Bahder" baseAuthorityYear="2021" box="[329,419,331,357]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Haplaxius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="356" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="delta">
<emphasis box="[329,419,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="356">H. delta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<emphasis box="[455,531,331,356]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="356">
<taxonomicName box="[455,528,331,356]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Myxia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="356" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Myxia</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
bringing the species count to three; 
<taxonomicName authority="Zumbado Echavarria &amp; Barrantes Barrantes &amp; Bartlett &amp; Helmick &amp; Bahder, 2021" authorityName="Zumbado Echavarria &amp; Barrantes Barrantes &amp; Bartlett &amp; Helmick &amp; Bahder" authorityYear="2021" box="[938,1076,331,357]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Myxia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="356" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="baynardi" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[938,1076,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="356">M. baynardi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1083,1146,331,357]" pageId="5" pageNumber="356">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1083,1146,331,357]" pageId="5" pageNumber="356" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1160,1281,331,357]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Myxia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="356" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="belinda">
<emphasis box="[1160,1281,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="356">M. belinda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Kramer, 1979)" authorityName="Zumbado Echavarria &amp; Barrantes Barrantes &amp; Bartlett &amp; Helmick &amp; Bahder" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Zumbado Echavarria &amp; Barrantes Barrantes &amp; Bartlett &amp; Helmick &amp; Bahder" baseAuthorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Haplaxius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="356" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="delta" status="new combination">
<emphasis box="[1343,1436,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="356">M. delta</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kramer, J. P." box="[159,315,367,393]" pageId="5" pageNumber="356" pagination="301 - 389" refId="ref7308" refString="Kramer, J. P. (1979) Taxonomic study of the planthopper genus Myndus in the Americas (Homoptera: Fulgoroidea: Cixiidae). Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 105 (3), 301 - 389. http: // www. jstor. org / stable / 25078242" type="journal article" year="1979">Kramer, 1979</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[328,531,366,393]" pageId="5" pageNumber="356">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[328,531,366,393]" pageId="5" pageNumber="356" rank="species">new combination</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
. The genus is now further supported with strong molecular support and consistent morphological characters among three taxa.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,609]" pageId="5" pageNumber="356">
Based on a combination of molecular and morphological evidence we place 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zumbado Echavarria &amp; Barrantes Barrantes &amp; Bartlett &amp; Helmick &amp; Bahder" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Zumbado Echavarria &amp; Barrantes Barrantes &amp; Bartlett &amp; Helmick &amp; Bahder" baseAuthorityYear="2021" box="[1048,1226,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Haplaxius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="356" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="delta">
<emphasis box="[1048,1226,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="356">Haplaxius delta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<taxonomicName box="[1260,1330,439,464]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Myxia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="356" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1260,1330,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="356">Myxia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as 
<taxonomicName authority="(Kramer, 1979)" authorityName="Zumbado Echavarria &amp; Barrantes Barrantes &amp; Bartlett &amp; Helmick &amp; Bahder" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Kramer" baseAuthorityYear="1979" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Myxia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="356" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="delta" status="new combination">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="356">Myxia delta</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kramer, J. P." box="[220,376,475,501]" pageId="5" pageNumber="356" pagination="301 - 389" refId="ref7308" refString="Kramer, J. P. (1979) Taxonomic study of the planthopper genus Myndus in the Americas (Homoptera: Fulgoroidea: Cixiidae). Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 105 (3), 301 - 389. http: // www. jstor. org / stable / 25078242" type="journal article" year="1979">Kramer, 1979</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[390,601,474,501]" pageId="5" pageNumber="356">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[390,596,474,501]" pageId="5" pageNumber="356" rank="species">new combination</taxonomicNameLabel>
.
</emphasis>
Both COI and 18S phylogenies have support for the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[1254,1324,475,500]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Myxia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="356" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1254,1324,475,500]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="356">Myxia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a clade (99 and 62 bootstrap support respectively with the consensus tree also providing support (95 bootstrap support). In all cases, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zumbado Echavarria &amp; Barrantes Barrantes &amp; Bartlett &amp; Helmick &amp; Bahder" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Kramer" baseAuthorityYear="1979" box="[257,346,547,573]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Myxia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="356" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="delta">
<emphasis box="[257,346,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="356">H. delta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resolved within the 
<taxonomicName box="[570,640,547,572]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Myxia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="356" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[570,640,547,572]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="356">Myxia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clade (
<figureCitation box="[719,801,547,573]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1551,1575]" captionTargetBox="[159,1428,181,1528]" captionTargetId="figure-24@10.[159,1428,181,1528]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 10. Aedeagus and periandrium of Myxia baynardi sp. n.: (A) right lateral view, (B), left lateral view, (C) dorsal view, and (D) ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4456538" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4456538/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="356">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
). Furthermore, the general form of the parameres, ventral process of the pygofer, and aedeagus are consistent with the 
<typeStatus box="[829,877,583,609]" pageId="5" pageNumber="356">type</typeStatus>
species, 
<taxonomicName box="[979,1140,583,609]" class="Insecta" family="Cixiidae" genus="Myxia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="356" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="belinda">
<emphasis box="[979,1140,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="356">Myxia belinda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
